@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor white
scale 2

title Activity Diagram: View Lap Time Comparison

|User|
start
:Request Lap Time Comparison;

|System|
:Retrieve selected drivers;
:Fetch lap time data for each driver\nfrom FastF1 API;

if (Lap time data available?) then (yes)
  :Process and align lap time data;
  :Calculate time differences;
  :Generate comparison chart\n(line chart with lap times);
  :Render chart on screen;

  |User|
  :Analyze lap time trends;
  :Identify fastest laps and\nperformance gaps;

else (no)
  :Display error message\n"Lap time data not available\nfor selected drivers";
endif

stop

@enduml

' ============================================================
' ACTIVITY DIAGRAM TEXT DESCRIPTION
' ============================================================
' Use Case: View Lap Time Comparison
'
' Step 1: The User requests lap time comparison view.
' Step 2: The System retrieves the list of selected drivers.
' Step 3: The System fetches lap time data for each selected
'         driver from the FastF1 API.
' Step 4: The System checks if lap time data is available.
'         - If NO: Display an error message indicating
'           lap time data is not available.
'         - If YES: Proceed to Step 5.
' Step 5: The System processes and aligns the lap time data
'         for all selected drivers.
' Step 6: The System calculates time differences between
'         drivers across laps.
' Step 7: The System generates a line chart visualizing
'         lap times for comparison.
' Step 8: The System renders the chart on the screen.
' Step 9: The User analyzes lap time trends and identifies
'         fastest laps and performance gaps between drivers.
' ============================================================
